---
description: How Cursor should respond
alwaysApply: true
---
- When asked to write code, ALWAYS show the full file path and complete file content.
- Before generating large changes, restate the goal in one sentence.
- If a request is ambiguous, ask one clarifying question before coding.
- Cite the specific file and line when modifying existing code.
- Do not invent libraries — if unsure whether a library exists, ask.
- Prefer standard library and the project's existing dependencies. Adding a new dep requires justification.
- After finishing a task, summarise: files changed, commands to verify, follow-up TODOs.
